article.headline: San Diego 65, Northern Kentucky 61
article.story: SAN DIEGO -- Dennis Kramer scored 15 points as San Diego held on to beat Northern Kentucky 65-61 on Wednesday night in the NUCDF Basketball Challenge at the Jenny Craig Pavilion in San Diego. Kramer was 4 of 5 from the field and led the Toreros in rebounds with six. Johnny Dee added 14 points for the Toreros (2-0). Chris Anderson finished the game with 13 points and six assists. San Diego shot 55 percent from the field in the first half and 50 percent for the game. San Diego led 30-26 at halftime in a game with five lead changes. Eshaunte Jones led the Norse with 12 points, including two 3-pointers, and six rebounds. Todd Johnson added 11 points and was 3 of 8 from 3-point range. Ernest Watson and Chad Jackson scored 9 points each for Northern Kentucky (0-1).
